      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So the main critique is just that it's not \"originalist.\" But when you look at the actual outcomes—like protecting privacy or marriage equality—it feels like the \"originalist\" view is essentially just a way to deny fundamental human rights that the founders couldn't have envisioned. Wouldn't you say that the originalist approach is fundamentally incapable of addressing modern civil rights issues?",
